<li id="cite_note-:0-54"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-:0_54-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-:0_54-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHjelm2010" class="citation book cs1">Hjelm, Ingrid (2010). "Mt. Gerizim and Samaritans in Recent Research". In Mor, Menachem; Reiterer, Friedrich V. (eds.). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/1059032652"><i>Samaritans - Past and Present: Current Studies</i></a>. De Gruyer. p.&#160;35. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-3-11-021283-9" title="Special:BookSources/978-3-11-021283-9"><bdi>978-3-11-021283-9</bdi></a>. <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1059032652">1059032652</a>. <q>The destruction of the Samaritan temple, Josephus argues, had taken place at the beginning of the reign of John Hyrcanus (135-104 BCE), rather than at the end of his reign. From the coinage, a dating later than 111 BCE is the more probable.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Mt.+Gerizim+and+Samaritans+in+Recent+Research&amp;rft.btitle=Samaritans+-+Past+and+Present%3A+Current+Studies&amp;rft.pages=35&amp;rft.pub=De+Gruyer&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F1059032652&amp;rft.isbn=978-3-11-021283-9&amp;rft.aulast=Hjelm&amp;rft.aufirst=Ingrid&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fworldcat.org%2Foclc%2F1059032652&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASecond+Temple+period" class="Z3988"></span></span>
